# Documentation Update Rules

When making any changes to the codebase, always update the documentation and translations accordingly.

## Documentation Updates

1. **Update source documentation**: Modify `.rst` files in `docs/docs/` to reflect code changes
2. **Update changelog**: Add entries to `docs/docs/changelog.rst` for significant changes

## Translation Workflow

1. **Generate translation templates** (only for local testing): Run `make gettext` in `docs/` to generate `.pot` files
2. **Update translation files** (only for local testing): Run `make update-po` to update `.po` files in `docs/locale/ru/LC_MESSAGES/`
3. **Translate new strings**: Edit Russian translations in `.po` files for any new or modified strings
4. **In repository**: Keep only `.po` files. Do not commit `.mo` files — Read the Docs compiles `.mo` during the documentation build (see `.readthedocs.yaml`)

## Cleanup After Testing

After running `make gettext`, `make update-po`, or building docs locally, always remove generated artifacts:

- **Remove build directory**: Delete `docs/_build/` (HTML, gettext, doctrees)
- **Remove all .mo files**: Delete every `*.mo` under `docs/locale/` (e.g. `docs/locale/**/*.mo`)
- **Use make clean**: Run `make clean` in `docs/` to remove build artifacts
- **Check git status**: Ensure no `_build/` or `.mo` files are staged or committed

## Workflow Example

```bash
# 1. Make code changes
# 2. Update .rst files in docs/docs/
# 3. (Optional, for testing) Update translations
cd docs
make gettext
make update-po
# 4. Edit .po files with new translations
# 5. (Optional) Test build
make html-all
# 6. Clean up: remove _build and all .mo files
make clean
# Remove .mo if present (e.g. del docs\locale\ru\LC_MESSAGES\**\*.mo on Windows)
cd ..
```

**Important**: Never commit `docs/_build/` or any `docs/locale/**/*.mo`. Only `.po` files belong in the repo; `.mo` is built on Read the Docs.
